<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC, EURATOM, ECSC) No 495/77 of 8 March 1977 determining the categories of officials entitled to, and the conditions for and rates of, allowances for regular stand-by duty </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 495/77, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks ametnike kategooriad, kellel on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist regulaarse valves olemise eest, ning nimetatud h&uuml;vitise andmise tingimused ja m&auml;&auml;rad 8. m&auml;rts 1977 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Staff Regulations of officials and the conditions of employment of other servants of the European Communities laid down in Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 259/68 (1), as last amended by Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 3178/76 (2), and in particular the second paragraph of Article 56b of the Staff Regulations, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirju ja &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimusi, mis on s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 259/68, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 3178/76, (2) eriti personalieeskirjade artikli 56b teist l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is for the Council, acting on a proposal from the Commission, to determine the categories of officials entitled to, and the conditions for and rates of, allowances which may be granted to officials who are regularly required to carry out stand-by duty at the place of employment or at home outside normal working hours, </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et n&otilde;ukogu &uuml;lesanne on komisjoni ettepaneku p&otilde;hjal m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks ametnike kategooriad, kellel on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist, mida v&otilde;ib maksta ametnikele, kes peavad olema regulaarselt valves oma t&ouml;&ouml;kohal v&otilde;i kodus v&auml;ljaspool tavalist t&ouml;&ouml;aega, ning m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks nimetatud h&uuml;vitise maksmise tingimused ja m&auml;&auml;rad, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Officials paid from appropriations in the research and investment budget and employed in an establishment of the Joint Research Centre or on indirect action, or paid from appropriations in the operating budget and employed to run or supervise technical installations or to work in the medical service, shall be entitled to an allowance when they are regularly required to carry out stand-by duty in accordance with Article 56b of the Staff Regulations. </inglise>
<eesti> Ametnikel, kellele makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tasu teadusuuringute ja investeeringute eelarvest ja kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad Teadusuuringute &Uuml;hiskeskuse asutuses v&otilde;i on h&otilde;lmatud kaudse tegevuse projektiga v&otilde;i kellele makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tasu tegevuseelarvest ja kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad tehniliste seadmete k&auml;itajate v&otilde;i j&auml;relevaatajatena v&otilde;i meditsiiniteenistuses, on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist, kui ta peab olema regulaarselt valves vastavalt personalieeskirjade artiklile 56b. </eesti>
<inglise> The allowance shall be determined as follows: (a) the allowance shall be expressed in points. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitis m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks j&auml;rgmiselt: a) h&uuml;vitis v&auml;ljendatakse punktides. </eesti>
<inglise> A point shall be equal to 0 7032 % of the basic salary of an official in Grade D4, step 1. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;ks punkt v&otilde;rdub 0,032 protsendiga palgaastme D4 1. j&auml;rgu ametniku p&otilde;hipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise> The allowance shall be adjusted by the weighting applicable to the official's remuneration; </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitist kohandatakse ametniku t&ouml;&ouml;tasu suhtes kohaldatava paranduskoefitsiendiga; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the number of points per hour of actual stand-by duty shall be: - for stand-by duty at the place of employment: 11 for working days and 22 for Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays; </inglise>
<eesti> b) tegelikult valves oldud aja eest saadavate punktide arv tunni kohta on j&auml;rgmine: - valve oma t&ouml;&ouml;kohal: t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evadel 11 ning laup&auml;eviti, p&uuml;hap&auml;eviti ja riigip&uuml;hadel 22; </eesti>
<inglise> - for stand-by duty at home: 2 715 for working days and 4 73 for Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays. </inglise>
<eesti> - valve kodus: t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evadel 2,15 ning laup&auml;eviti, p&uuml;hap&auml;eviti ja riigip&uuml;hadel 4,3; </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> No allowance shall be granted for stand-by duty at home if the actual period of duty does not amount to at least 14 hours. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitist ei anta kodus valves oldud aja eest, kui tegelik valves oldud aeg on l&uuml;hem kui 14 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> An official who can show that for a period not exceeding one month he was prevented from doing stand-by duty at the place of employment as a result of illness or accident, or because he was on annual leave, shall retain his entitlement to the allowance. </inglise>
<eesti> Ametnik, kes suudab t&otilde;endada, et ta ei saanud kuni kuu pikkuse ajavahemiku jooksul olla t&ouml;&ouml;kohal valves haiguse v&otilde;i &otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i p&otilde;hipuhkusel oleku t&otilde;ttu, s&auml;ilitab &otilde;iguse h&uuml;vitisele. </eesti>
<inglise> If he is prevented from doing stand-by duty for more than one month owing to sickness or accident, his entitlement to the allowance shall be suspended at the end of the first month until he resumes work. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui haiguse v&otilde;i &otilde;nnetuse t&otilde;ttu ei saa ametnik valves olla rohkem kui &uuml;he kuu pikkuse ajavahemiku jooksul, peatatakse tema &otilde;igus h&uuml;vitisele esimese kuu l&otilde;pus seniks, kuni ta taasalustab t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> For the period referred to in the previous subparagraph, the official shall be entitled to an allowance of 42 points for each day of absence due to sickness or accident for which he has a medical certificate, or for each day of annual leave. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelmises l&otilde;igus nimetatud ajavahemiku jooksul on ametnikul &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist 42 punkti ulatuses iga haiguse v&otilde;i &otilde;nnetuse t&otilde;ttu puudutud p&auml;eva eest, mille kohta tal on esitada arstit&otilde;end, v&otilde;i iga p&otilde;hipuhkuse p&auml;eva eest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall apply by analogy to temporary, auxiliary and establishment staff. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse analoogia p&otilde;hjal ajutiste, abi- ja koosseisuliste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> In April each year, the Commission shall submit to the Council a report on the number of officials and servants in each category who have received the allowance referred to in this Regulation. (1) OJ No L 56, 4.3.1968, p. 1. (2) OJ No L 359, 30.12.1976, p. 9. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga aasta aprillis esitab komisjon n&otilde;ukogule ettekande selle kohta, kui palju ametnikke ja teenistujaid igas kategoorias on k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses kirjeldatud h&uuml;vitist saanud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Council Regulation (Euratom) No 1371/72 of 27 June 1972 determining the rates and conditions of the special allowances which may be granted to officials or servants who are paid from appropriations in the research and investment budget and employed in an establishment of the Joint Research Centre or on indirect action, for certain services of a special nature (1), is hereby repealed. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1972. aasta m&auml;&auml;rus (Euratom) nr 1371/72, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks teadusuuringute ja investeeringute eelarvest t&ouml;&ouml;tasu saavatele ja Teadusuuringute &Uuml;hiskeskuse asutuses t&ouml;&ouml;tavatele v&otilde;i kaudse tegevuse projektiga h&otilde;lmatud ametnikele ja teenistujatele teatavate eriliste t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete eest makstavate erih&uuml;vitiste m&auml;&auml;rad ja maksmise tingimused, (3) tunnistatakse kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 8 March 1977. </inglise>
